OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780002672
OL,3,CJudge told boy rapists 'akin' to past
OL,4,Ccase of teenager jailed for eight years
OL,6,FA third boy, now aged 14, was also
OL,7,Fconvicted of rape for his involvement
OL,8,Fin the second attack and an indecent
OL,9,Fimages offence.
OL,11,FThe sentences of the three teenage
OL,12,Fboys are being sent to the Court of
OL,13,FAppeal after a review under the Unduly
OL,14,FLenient Sentences (ULS) scheme.
OL,16,FAttorney General Lord Hermer said
OL,17,Fthere was "an epidemic of violence
OL,18,Fagainst women and girls in this
OL,19,Fcountry" after Sir Keir Starmer
OL,20,Fannounced the "distressing" case would
OL,21,Fbe referred following a public outcry.
OL,26,@yD@KOU{D@HO]|D@OOU|D@[O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/13
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780002672
OL,3,CJudge told boy rapists 'akin' to past
OL,4,Ccase of teenager jailed for eight years
OL,6,FIn a copy of the sentencing note
OL,7,Fprepared for the hearing by prosecutor
OL,8,FJodie Mittell KC, it quotes the case
OL,9,Flaw of a previous case involving a 15-
OL,10,Fyear-old boy convicted of three rapes,
OL,11,Fdigital penetration and sexual assault.
OL,13,FIn her note, obtained by the Press
OL,14,FAssociation, Ms Mittell ` who herself
OL,15,Fsits as a recorder ` states that "on
OL,16,Fbalance, (the previous case) is akin
OL,17,Fto this case, with features that vary
OL,18,Fin seriousness".
OL,26,@wD@bOUzD@OO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/13
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780002672
OL,3,CJudge told boy rapists 'akin' to past
OL,4,Ccase of teenager jailed for eight years
OL,6,FShe outlines that there were four
OL,7,Fcomplainants in the previous case `
OL,8,Faged 13, 14 and 15 ` and the offences
OL,9,Foccurred after the defendant "met the
OL,10,Fcomplainants after first contacting
OL,11,Fthem online", with the offences taking
OL,12,Fplace in a wooded area and in a public
OL,13,Flavatory.
OL,26,@qD@^OUsD@LO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/13
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780002672
OL,3,CJudge told boy rapists 'akin' to past
OL,4,Ccase of teenager jailed for eight years
OL,6,FMs Mittell states in the note, which
OL,7,Fwas not read out loud in court but
OL,8,Fpresented digitally to the judge, that
OL,9,Fthe sentence of a eight-year custodial
OL,10,Fterm with a six-year extended licence
OL,11,Fwas given to the boy who was 16 at the
OL,12,Ftime of sentence after the judge in
OL,13,Fthat case "applied the adult
OL,14,Fguidelines".
OL,16,FIn her note to Judge Rowland, Ms
OL,17,FMittell said that the circumstances of
OL,18,Fthe Fordingbridge attacks were
OL,19,Fsufficient "to elevate the offence to
OL,20,Fcategory 1 harm" ` the highest level
OL,21,Ffor sentencing.
OL,26,@uD@KOUvD@KO]{D@LOU|D@PO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/13
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780002672
OL,3,CJudge told boy rapists 'akin' to past
OL,4,Ccase of teenager jailed for eight years
OL,6,FShe said that these factors included
OL,7,F"vulnerable" victims, "additional
OL,8,Fdegradation/humiliation (comments from
OL,9,Fthose present)", "violence or threats
OL,10,Fof violence beyond that which is
OL,11,Finherent in the offence" and
OL,12,F"psychological harm to be determined".
OL,14,FMs Mittell added that the "significant
OL,15,Fdegree of planning" by befriending the
OL,16,Ffirst victim online, acting with
OL,17,Fothers to commit the offence and
OL,18,Frecording of the offence put the
OL,19,Foffences into "culpability category A"
OL,20,Fwith the "location and timing of the
OL,21,Foffence" being aggravating factors.
OL,26,@oD@AOUoD@LO]oD@WOUqD@OO]qD@ROUsD@XO]tD@
OL,26,AAOUtD@eO]vD@[OUwD@SO]{D@OOU{D@fO]|D@JOU
OL,26,B}D@HO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/13
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780002672
OL,3,CJudge told boy rapists 'akin' to past
OL,4,Ccase of teenager jailed for eight years
OL,6,FShe advised that the guideline
OL,7,Fsentencing ranges for a catergory 1A
OL,8,Foffence was 12-19 years' custody with
OL,9,Fa starting point of 15 years.
OL,11,FOr if the offences were considered to
OL,12,Fbe a lower category 2A then the range
OL,13,Fwould be nine to 13 years' custody
OL,14,Fwith a starting point of 10 years'
OL,15,Fcustody.
OL,17,FShe added that the offence of taking
OL,18,Findecent images of children also came
OL,19,Fwith a guideline sentence of four to
OL,20,Fnine years' custody with a starting
OL,21,Fpoint of six years.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/13
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780002672
OL,3,CJudge told boy rapists 'akin' to past
OL,4,Ccase of teenager jailed for eight years
OL,6,FHowever, Ms Mittell said the
OL,7,Fguidelines stated that "a custodial
OL,8,Fsentence must only be imposed as a
OL,9,Fmeasure of last resort; statute
OL,10,Fprovides that such a sentence may be
OL,11,Fimposed only when an offence is so
OL,12,Fserious that neither a fine alone nor
OL,13,Fa community sentence can be justified".
OL,26,@oD@XOUuD@fO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/13
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780002672
OL,3,CJudge told boy rapists 'akin' to past
OL,4,Ccase of teenager jailed for eight years
OL,6,FShe added that the guidelines state if
OL,7,Fthe court was satisfied that the
OL,8,Foffences "crosses the custody
OL,9,Fthreshold and that no other sentence
OL,10,Fis appropriate, the court may as a
OL,11,Fpreliminary consideration, consult the
OL,12,Fequivalent adult guideline in order to
OL,13,Fdecide upon the appropriate length of
OL,14,Fsentence".
OL,26,@pD@JOUvD@IO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/13
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780002672
OL,3,CJudge told boy rapists 'akin' to past
OL,4,Ccase of teenager jailed for eight years
OL,6,FAnd she said that the guidelines add:
OL,7,F"When considering the relevant adult
OL,8,Fguideline, the court may feel
OL,9,Finappropriate to apply a sentence
OL,10,Fbroadly within the region of half to
OL,11,Ftwo-thirds of the adult sentence for
OL,12,Fthose age 15-17 and allow a greater
OL,13,Freduction for those under 15. This is
OL,14,Fonly a rough guide."
OL,16,FA spokesman for the Crown Prosecution
OL,17,FService (CPS), which Ms Mittell
OL,18,Frepresented in court, said that it was
OL,19,Famong those who had referred the case
OL,20,Fto the attorney general under the ULS
OL,21,Fscheme.
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@TO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G10/13
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780002672
OL,3,CJudge told boy rapists 'akin' to past
OL,4,Ccase of teenager jailed for eight years
OL,6,FIn an interview with BBC Newsnight,
OL,7,Fone of the victims ` who is now 15,
OL,8,Fsaid of Judge Rowland's sentencing
OL,9,Fcomments: "Why would you avoid
OL,10,Fcriminalising someone who has done a
OL,11,Fcriminal act?
OL,13,F"They did it, they need to understand
OL,14,Fthat their actions do have
OL,15,Fconsequences and they can't just get
OL,16,Faway with not being criminalised."
OL,26,@qD@KOUuD@AOUxD@bO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G11/13
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41412
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780002672
OL,3,CJudge told boy rapists 'akin' to past
OL,4,Ccase of teenager jailed for eight years
OL,6,FDiscussing how the crimes had affected
OL,7,Fher, the girl said: "I feel like no
OL,8,Fmatter what I do, I can always feel
OL,9,Ftheir hands on me, no matter how much
OL,10,FI've scrubbed, how much I've tried to
OL,11,Fget the feeling away it's always there
OL,12,Fand it just doesn't feel like my body
OL,13,Fanymore."
OL,15,FThe girl's father said the family felt
OL,16,F"anger" over the sentences and that it
OL,17,Fwas "heartbreaking" to see his
OL,18,Fdaughter's confidence "drop to a low"
OL,19,Fand called for the boys to be given a
OL,20,Fcustodial sentence of a minimum of two
OL,21,Fyears.
OL,26,@oD@UOUuD@IO]xD@AOUxD@GO]yD@EOUyD@SO]zD@
OL,26,AWOUzD@eO]
